title: The FBI Takes AIM (KPFA, 1978)
description:
Original: https://archive.org/details/cueth_000296
H.K. Yuen Collection, UC Berkeley http://www.oac.cdlib.org/findaid/ark:/13030/kt9j49s39b/
The FBI Takes AIM: Jack Schwartz (a lawyer for American Indian Movement) speaks on the FBI and Bureau of Indian Affairs involvement in the trials resulting from Wounded Knee and the case of Paul Skyhorse/Richard Mohawk.

For more related content, please visit: 
http://ourhiddenhistory.org/
